docs.summary:
Upgrades or downgrades a Wix service that is included in a package. For example, you can upgrade a `Business Unlimited Premium` plan to `Business VIP` using this endpoint.

> **Notes:**
> * It is up to the reseller to decide whether the adjustment should effect the customer’s payment.
> * You can only adjust a product to another product of the same type. See [Wix Premium Subscriptions](https://support.wix.com/en/article/choosing-a-premium-plan) for more details.
> * The customer has immediate access to new features, while loosing access to features not included in the new service.
> * If a removed feature is a requirement for another service, that service may not function any longer. For example, if you downgrade a `Business Unlimited` plan to `Business Basic`, the site owners won’t be able to use `Pro eCommerce Features` any longer.

> **Important**: This call requires an account level API key and cannot be authenticated with the standard authorization header. API keys are currently available to selected beta users only.

extra.description: Change a product of an existing product instance

docs.summary:
Cancels all services included in the package.

> **Note:** If a canceled service is a requirement for another product instance, that functionality may not be available to the customer any longer. For example, if you cancel a Premium plan, a previously connected domain will be disconnected from the site.  
> **Important**: This call requires an account level API key and cannot be authenticated with the standard authorization header. API keys are currently available to selected beta users only.

Cancels a service.

> * The customer immediately looses access to features included in the canceled service.
> * If a canceled service is a requirement for another service, that service may not be available to the customer any longer. For example, if you cancel a `Combo Plan` plan, a previously connected domain will be disconnected from the site.


> **Important**: This call requires an account level API key and cannot be authenticated with the standard authorization header. API keys are currently available to selected beta users only.

members.name: offset
members.doc: Number of items to skip in the current sort order.

members.name: cursor
members.doc:
Pointer to the next or previous page in the list of results.

You can get the relevant cursor token
from the `pagingMetadata` object in the previous call's response.
Not relevant for the first request.

members.name: count
members.doc: Number of items returned in the response.

members.name: total
members.doc: Total number of items that match the query. Returned if offset paging is used and the `tooManyToCount` flag is not set.

members.name: tooManyToCount
members.doc: Flag that indicates the server failed to calculate the `total` field.

members.name: cursors
members.doc: Cursors to navigate through the result pages using `next` and `prev`. Returned if cursor paging is used.

members.name: next
members.doc: Cursor pointing to next page in the list of results.

members.name: prev
members.doc: Cursor pointing to previous page in the list of results.

members.name: fieldName
members.doc: Name of the field to sort by.

members.name: filter
sort
members.doc:
Sort object in the following format:  
`[{"fieldName":"sortField1","order":"ASC"},{"fieldName":"sortField2","order":"DESC"}]`

members.name: fields
members.doc: Array of projected fields. A list of specific field names to return. If `fieldsets` are also specified, the union of `fieldsets` and `fields` is returned.

members.name: fieldsets
members.doc: Array of named, predefined sets of projected fields. A array of predefined named sets of fields to be returned. Specifying multiple `fieldsets` will return the union of fields from all sets. If `fields` are also specified, the union of `fieldsets` and `fields` is returned.

members.name: paging
members.doc: Paging options to limit and skip the number of items.

members.name: cursorPaging
members.doc: Cursor token pointing to a page of results. Not used in the first request. Following requests use the cursor token and not `filter` or `sort`.

  • DAY - day
  • WEEK - week
  • MONTH - month
  • YEAR - year

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • ONE_TIME
  • RECURRING

Possible values are:
  • PENDING
  • ENABLED
  • CANCELED
  • FAILED

Possible values are:
  • ASC
  • DESC

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN - unknown interval unit
  • DAY - day
  • WEEK - week
  • MONTH - month
  • YEAR - year

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • SBS
  • LICENSER
  • BASS
  • RESELLER

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • AUTO_RENEW_ON - Subscription will be renewed automatically at the end of the current payment cycle
  • AUTO_RENEW_OFF - Subscription will not be renewed at the end of the current payment cycle
  • MANUAL_RECURRING - Subscription will require user to manually renew
  • CANCELLED - Subscription has been cancelled
  • TRANSFERRED - Subscription has been transferred to a different account

Copied from SBS Possible values are:
  • NOT_APPLICABLE
  • ADDITIONAL_QUANTITY
  • CREDIT_UNUSED_PERIOD
  • REFUND_PRICE_DIFF
  • ADJUST_PERIOD_END
  • DOWNGRADE_GRACE_PERIOD
  • FULL_AMOUNT_PERIOD
  • END_OF_PERIOD
  • PENDING_CHANGES
  • DOWNGRADE_RENEWAL

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • USER_REQUESTED - initiated by the user
  • REPLACED_BY_ANOTHER_SUBSCRIPTION - Another subscription was assigned to the site this subscription was assigned to
